column5: Those buggers can be tough. Fished all afternoon yesterday and we had one bite. This was it and it happened to be on my buddy's birthday. A smaller 35" fish, but at least we caught one. I never had a bite.
This was a surprise last minute catch. Amazing what will hit a muskie bait trolled at a higher speed.
always nice when the birthday guy gets a catch. thanks for sharing jim.  cheers
I never mind getting skunked if I can put a buddy on a fish. A nice bday present
ive always said, that a fish in the boat is the boat's fish. Its a team effort out there.  Well done.
Interesting.  Last year I had a 20" LargeMouth hit my Double-Cow girl on Nippissing. Nice to see some folks are catching some ski's this year.
ive always said, that a fish in the boat is the boat's fish. Its a team effort out there.  Well done. Always this.
That looks like a Musky...they must be related.
With muskie fishing, you are always only 1 fish away from a boom/bust day
Thats why I fish bass. LOL  Nice bonus for his BDay.

I've had two PB's of other species (LM and SM bass) while trolling for muskie this year. Can't say I've been very successful for muskie, just a couple small ones, but it's crazy that bass will still hit a 8" lure being trolled along at 6mph!
That looks like a Musky...they must be related. It is but we always dream of multiple fish days.
